  "notes": "Uninitialized array allocation.",
  "notes_sections": [
    "Unlike other array creation functions (e.g. `zeros`, `ones`, `full`), `empty` does not initialize the values of the array, and may therefore be marginally faster. However, the values stored in the newly allocated array are arbitrary. For reproducible behavior, be sure to set each element of the array before reading."
  ],
  "numpy_ref": "np.empty",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "body": [
        "Shape of the empty array, e.g., ``(2, 3)`` or ``2``."
      ],
      "name": "shape",
      "type": "int or tuple of int"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "Desired output data-type for the array, e.g, `fnp.int8`. Default is",
        "`fnp.float64`."
      ],
      "name": "dtype",
      "type": "data-type, optional"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "Whether to store multi-dimensional data in row-major",
        "(C-style) or column-major (Fortran-style) order in memory."
      ],
      "name": "order",
      "type": "{'C', 'F'}, optional, default: 'C'"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "The device on which to place the created array. Default: ``None``.",
        "For Array-API interoperability only, so must be ``\"cpu\"`` if passed.",
        "",
        ".. versionadded:: 2.0.0"
      ],
      "name": "device",
      "type": "str, optional"
    },
    {
      "body": [
        "Reference object to allow the creation of arrays which are not",
        "NumPy arrays. If an array-like passed in as ``like`` supports",
